Serving Civil Lawsuit to Donators of CanadaLandShow

The database of the CanadalandShow donors was obtained legally via a US Federal Judge court subpoena. When granting the motion to reveal the names, addresses and other financial information of the CanadaLandShow.com contributors, US Federal Courts decided donors are legally responsible for libelous defamation acts committed by the organization they support. In Judge Grant's decision he wrote: "The same laws forbidding the financial support of conventional terror also pertains to digital terror."
